# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# OEDON — Declarative Application Registry (apps.list)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Format: name | internal-port | domain
#
# Rules:
#   - The "name" must match the Docker container name
#     (container_name in its docker-compose.yml) and its position
#     in oedon-network. Nginx resolves the container by that name.
#
#   - The "port" is the INTERNAL port that the app exposes within
#     the Docker network, not to the host. It is not necessary to publish it in ports:.
#
#   - The "domain" can be local (*.oedon.test) or real (app.yourdomain.com).
#
# To apply changes:
#   ./scripts/sync-apps.sh
#
# To preview without applying:
#   ./scripts/sync-apps.sh --dry-run
#
# To deploy a single app manually:
#   ./scripts/deploy.sh <name> <port> <domain>
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Name             | Port  | Domain
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
oedon-static      | 80     | static.oedon.test
wordpress-app     | 9000   | wordpress.oedon.test
python-app        | 5000   | python.oedon.test

# Examples of future apps (uncomment when deployed):
# pulse           | 8080   | gestion.oedon.test
# moodle          | 8080   | lms.oedon.test
# gitea           | 3000   | git.oedon.test
